title: WORK IN PROGRESS
description: A Four-Year Project of Drone Photographs of Construction Sites in Atlanta.

title: LIMINAL
description: The word Liminal means to be at or on both sides of a boundary, it refers to the beginning or start of a process. Liminal spaces are there to be moved through, like train stations and airports, they are not destinations of their own, they're the start of a journey that will take us somewhere else.

title: OFF DAYS
description: Photographed mostly in the Southern United States, Shaw's wry black and white images depict people and places that are neither idealized nor embellished; Shaw pulls back the  curtain on the idyllic suburban American dream to reveal its sobering underside. title: EDGE
description: EDGE is one of those rare books that come along that will change the way you see the world. title: INK
description: Ink showcases an unusual body of work by Tanya Marcuse which came about serendipitously after her young son insisted on trying nocturnal squid fishing one summer in Maine. Unlike the majority of Marcuse’s large-scale, elaborate works, these images were made with an iPhone camera, a more spontaneous and versatile tool.

description: Black Diamonds is a personal endeavor to connect with the Appalachian region Facun now calls home. description: A lyrical document about the fragile miracle of life. The 13th Spring was made between 2014-2016 after Hardin discovered that his wife was unexpectedly pregnant for the first time. title: PAST TIME
description: Past Time explores the political and cultural idealization of an America that never existed for many. description: The advent of smartphones has conditioned new reflexes and created a new, unsettling gestural vocabulary that evokes a near-mystical posture. description: Sweetheart Roller Skating Rink is a royal road to that special time in 1972-1973—when the love generation in America was at its height. title: ALPHABET
description: This sumptuous case-bound book features 26 black and white photographs, each corresponding with a letter of the alphabet. Pulled from Caffery’s deep archive, this book creatively reimagines the essential childhood experience of learning the ABC’s.

description: Bottom of da Boot focuses on the people and places of the disappearing communities of Isle de Jean Charles and Pointe-aux-Chenes on Louisiana's fragile coastline.
